Hello and welcome back to The Best & The Brightest. I=E2=80=99m Leigh Ann
Caldwell, writing from a nondescript courthouse in Washington, D.C., as I w=
ait to hear if I=E2=80=99m one of the lucky ones chosen to sit on a jury. (=
My partner Eriq Gardner, Puck=E2=80=99s legal eminence, should hopefully be=
 able to make a call or two to get me out of here=E2=80=A6) Alas, with two =
local courts, the D.C. Circuit federal court, and a relatively small juror =
pool, Washington residents know that an annual jury summons is as reliable =
as the cherry blossoms.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

I checked in with sources today, plenty of whom are asking me whether Mike =
Johnson will have the votes to pass the six-month spending bill in the Hous=
e tomorrow. Currently, it feels like Johnson (really, Trump) will be able t=
o unite Republicans on the bill. Below, Abby Livingston runs through the nu=
mbers. Our partner Bill Cohan also
offers his assessment on Trump=E2=80=99s bluster about creating a crypto Fo=
rt Knox.

=C2=A0

But first=E2=80=A6

