ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">We=E2=80=99ll see. Assuming the Trump-Johnson theory of House Republica=
ns holds, the operative
question in the Senate will be whether six or seven Democrats, depending on=
 <strong>Rand Paul</strong>=E2=80=99s whims, will join with Senate Republic=
ans to override a filibuster and keep the government open. If Suozzi appear=
ed a persuadable Dem for House Republicans, then Michigan freshman Democrat=
 <strong>Elissa Slotkin</strong> should be his Senate counterpart: She and =
Trump both won Michigan on the same ballot in 2024. But Slotkin was also a =
clear =E2=80=9Cno=E2=80=9D on Sunday, when she told <em>Meet the
Press</em> that =E2=80=9Cthe president has been deciding how to spend the m=
oney any way he wants even when we have a budget that both Democrats and Re=
publicans voted on.=E2=80=9D She said she would withhold her vote in the ab=
sence of assurances that the money would be spent the way Congress intends.=
 =E2=80=9CEveryone knows Congress has the power of the purse,=E2=80=9D she =
said.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin:0;">Still, when it comes to the all-important metric of <em>vibes</em>,=
 many
Democrats I spoke with on Monday seemed to think a shutdown would be avoide=
d=E2=80=94that, in the end, enough Senate Democrats would back a Republican=
 spending bill to keep the government open, even though it=E2=80=99s hard t=
o see right now where those votes would come from. Their logic is as follow=
s: First, securing a compromise on spending amid a shutdown might actually =
lead to a <em>worse </em>outcome relative to current spending levels, which=
 were passed when Democrats controlled the White House and Senate.
And second, what good would a clause attempting to rein in Trump and Musk r=
eally do? =E2=80=9CHe=E2=80=99s <em>already</em> breaking the law,=E2=80=9D=
 a senior Democratic Hill aide told me. =E2=80=9CWhat are we gonna do, pass=
 a super law?=E2=80=9D</p></div>
